-- Mechel Seeks to Buy Kureinsky Coal Deposit, Kommersant Reports
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-08-29T05:15:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-29/mechel-seeks-to-buy-kureinsky-coal-deposit-kommersant-reports.html
OAO  Mechel (MTLR) ,  Russia ’s largest
producer of coal for steelmakers, is seeking to buy the
Kureinsky coal deposit from a joint venture of steelmakers  Evraz
Plc (EVR)  and OAO Magnitogorsk Iron & Steel,  Kommersant  reported.  Kureinsky, in Siberia’s Kemerovo region, has about 60
million metric tons of coking coal reserves and may cost as much
as $40 million, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  